26/11/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The last 2,413 conscript soldiers in Bulgaria were discharged on Sunday (November 25th) marking the end of mandatory military service.
Starting on December 1st, the Bulgarian army will be fully professional and number between 31,000 and 39,000.
The soldiers' discharge, which happened a month earlier than scheduled under a proposal by Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov, was marked with ceremonies in Sofia and four other large cities.
(Sofia News Agency, Reuters, B92, BTV, Monitor, BNT - 25/11/07)
